1.2. Creating a ggplot in first layer

# 
test <- ggplot(data = mpg)


1.3. To see the relationship between displ and hwy

    (displ)(hwy)
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))


note : 

    ggplot(No side effect)(Global Environment)ggplot(Local Environment)mpgggplotLocal Environmentx-axis, y-axisaes(x = displ, y = hwy)aes(x = mpg$displ, y = mpg$hwy)


2. Aesthetic mappings for unordered variable


2.1. unordered variable

    
# find the outlier
ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
   geom_point(mapping = aes(color = displ > 5 & hwy > 20))


# class
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, color = class))


# sizeclassclass
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, size = class))
## Warning: Using size for a discrete variable is not advised.

2.2. ordered variable


# 
 ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, color = cyl))



2.2.1. Size and color work with continuous variables, they just display a gradient.
- Shape does not work with continuous variables.
 ggplot(data = mpg) + 
        geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, size = cty, color = cty, alpha = cty))



2.2.2. Its not very helpful to use multiple aes in 2 Dimensions variables.
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
        geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy), shape = 21, stroke = 4)


#  aes() 
test <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy), color = "blue")


3. Geometric objects


# 
x <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))

# 
y <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_line(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))

# 
z <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))

ggplot2.multiplot(x,y,z, cols=1)
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'


# linetype
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, linetype = drv))
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'


3.1. global mappings

ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'


3.2. place multiple geoms in the same plot

ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, color = drv)) +
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth(aes(linetype = drv))
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'


ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(color = class)) + 
  geom_smooth(data = filter(mpg, class == "subcompact"), se = FALSE)

4. Facets


4.1. facet_grid(row ~ column)

ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  facet_wrap(~ class, nrow = 2)


ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  facet_grid(drv ~ cyl)


ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  facet_wrap(~ cty, nrow = 3)


4.2. Exercises

a <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = drv, y = cyl))

b <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) +
  facet_grid(drv ~ .)

ggplot2.multiplot(a,b, cols=1)

c <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) +
  facet_grid(. ~ cyl)

d <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  facet_wrap(~ class, nrow = 2)



ggplot2.multiplot(c,d, cols=1)

  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut))


ggplot(data = diamonds) + 
  geom_pointrange(
    mapping = aes(x = cut, y = depth),
    stat = "summary",
    fun.ymin = min,
    fun.ymax = max,
    fun.y = median
  )


6. Statistical Transformations


6.1. Position adjustments

a <- ggplot(data = diamonds) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut, colour = cut))
b <- ggplot(data = diamonds) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut, fill = cut))

ggplot2.multiplot(a,b, cols = 2)


ggplot(data = diamonds) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut, fill = clarity))


ggplot(data = diamonds, mapping = aes(x = cut, fill = clarity)) + 
  geom_bar(alpha = 1/5, position = "identity")

ggplot(data = diamonds, mapping = aes(x = cut, colour = clarity)) + 
  geom_bar(fill = NA, position = "identity")


ggplot(data = diamonds) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut, fill = clarity), position = "fill")


ggplot(data = diamonds) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut, fill = clarity), position = "dodge")
